<subSubSection id="C376651EFFA9FFA5E188EAFFFA3B02EC" pageId="5" pageNumber="249" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD33695FFA9FFA5E188EAFFFCD6020B" blockId="5.[151,1437,759,1218]" pageId="5" pageNumber="249">
<emphasis id="B918EA87FFA9FFA5E188EAFFFEE50598" bold="true" box="[199,332,975,1002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="249">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C6C4D16FFA9FFA5E01CEAE0FD8E059B" box="[339,551,976,1002]" class="Insecta" family="Rhyparochromidae" genus="Bubaces" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="249" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castaneus">
<emphasis id="B918EA87FFA9FFA5E01CEAE0FD8E059B" box="[339,551,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="249">Bubaces castaneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus id="54D78837FFA9FFA5E311EAE0FD270598" box="[606,654,976,1002]" pageId="5" pageNumber="249">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus, is segregated by having the dorsal surface of the pronotum, clavi and coria glabrous, the coria lack the circular yellow to creamy-yellow subapical spots, the head ventrally has a shallow longitudinal sulcus, the rostrum reaches the posterior border of abdominal sternite IV, all tibiae are sparsely spined, and the ostiolar peritremes in male specimens are raised, above the pleural surface, posteriorly with a gentle and open curve, resembling a question mark.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD33695FFA9FFA5E188EDB3FA3B02EC" blockId="5.[151,1437,759,1218]" box="[199,1426,1155,1182]" pageId="5" pageNumber="249">
